                                  levels=c("Grass/Shrubland", "Broadleaf/mixed forest", "Conifer forest", "Boreal forest"), 
                                  ordered=T)

Relative area (%) in which LSF is increasing

##########
#Per biome
##########

total_area   = aggregate(climate_tab$pixelArea, 
                         by=list(Category=climate_tab$biome), 
                         FUN=sum)
                               
Increase     = aggregate(climate_tab[climate_tab$Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster > 0, ]
                         $pixelArea, 
               by=list(Category=climate_tab[climate_tab$Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster > 0, ]
                       $biome), 
               FUN=sum)[2] / total_area[2]

IncreaseSign = aggregate(climate_tab[climate_tab$Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster > 0 
                & climate_tab$Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster < 0.05, ]$pixelArea,
               by=list(Category=climate_tab[climate_tab$Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster > 0 
                & climate_tab$Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster < 0.05, ]$biome), 
               FUN=sum)[2] / total_area[2]

DecreaseSign = aggregate(climate_tab[climate_tab$Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster < 0 
                & climate_tab$Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster < 0.05, ]$pixelArea,
               by=list(Category=climate_tab[climate_tab$Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster < 0 
                & climate_tab$Pvalue_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster < 0.05, ]$biome), 
               FUN=sum)[2] / total_area[2]

#create table
biomeTab        = cbind(total_area[1], Increase, IncreaseSign, DecreaseSign)
names(biomeTab) = c("Continent", "Increase", "IncreaseSign", "DecreaseSign")

#write table
write.table(biomeTab, file=paste(output.dir, "frost_change_biomes.csv", sep="/"), 
            col.names=TRUE, row.names=FALSE, quote=FALSE, sep=",")

Figure S1ef:

########################################################
#create table with standardized correlation coefficients
########################################################

standard             <- function(x) (x - mean(x, na.rm=T)) / (2*sd(x, na.rm=T))
climate_tab$category <- paste(climate_tab$biome, climate_tab$continent_sub, sep="_")
categories           <- unique(climate_tab$category)

CoeffDataFrame        <- data.frame(VariableNames = categories)
FrostRiskVect         <- vector()
FrostChangeVect       <- vector()
FrostRiskCI           <- vector()
FrostChangeCI         <- vector()

for (category in categories) {
    tab.sub             <- climate_tab[climate_tab$category==category,]
    FrostRiskFormula    <- as.formula(standard(Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostZero)~standard(Q95_DegreeZeroToFrostFour))
    FrostChangeFormula  <- as.formula(standard(Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostZero_Max_raster)~
                                        standard(Slope_of_Global_DegreeZeroToFrostFour_Max_raster))
    
    # train single linear models for the categories
    CoeffFrostRisk      <- summary(lm(FrostRiskFormula,   data=tab.sub))$coefficients[2]
    CIfrostRisk         <- summary(lm(FrostRiskFormula,   data=tab.sub))$coefficients[4]*2
    CoeffFrostChange    <- summary(lm(FrostChangeFormula, data=tab.sub))$coefficients[2]
    CIfrostChange       <- summary(lm(FrostChangeFormula, data=tab.sub))$coefficients[4]*2
    
    # append this to the vector
    FrostRiskVect       <- append(FrostRiskVect,   CoeffFrostRisk)
    FrostChangeVect     <- append(FrostChangeVect, CoeffFrostChange)
    FrostRiskCI         <- append(FrostRiskCI,     CIfrostRisk)
    FrostChangeCI       <- append(FrostChangeCI,   CIfrostChange)
}

# cbind the name and coefficients into a data frame
CoeffDataFrame = data.frame(CoeffDataFrame, FrostRiskVect, FrostChangeVect, FrostRiskCI, FrostChangeCI)

#Split category column into biomes and continents
CoeffDataFrame <- tidyr::separate(CoeffDataFrame, col = "VariableNames", into = c("biome", "continent"), sep = "_")

#order biomes and continents
CoeffDataFrame$continent = factor(CoeffDataFrame$continent, 
         levels=c("North America", "South America", "Europe", "West Asia", "East Asia"),ordered=T)
CoeffDataFrame$biome = factor(CoeffDataFrame$biome, 
         levels=c("Grass/Shrubland", "Broadleaf/mixed forest", "Conifer forest", "Boreal forest"),ordered=T)

  theme(#legend.position= "NA",
        legend.background = element_rect(fill=NA,
